# Agent Coordination

## Stop and Confirm at Milestones

For multi-host or multi-stage tasks: complete the first unit (e.g. the first host, Wave 1), present the result, and **stop**. Wait for explicit confirmation before proceeding. Never batch-apply across all targets without an intermediate checkpoint.

For builds: build the primary machine (mike) first, show the result, then wait before building others.

## Design Tasks for Parallel Execution

When breaking a large task into todos, identify which ones touch disjoint files and can run concurrently. Label them with a wave or stream. Each todo should own a clearly bounded set of files so agents never conflict.

## Use Worktrees for Isolated Work

For feature work, operate in a git worktree on a dedicated feature branch rather than the main working tree. For parallel multi-agent tasks, each agent works in its own temporary worktree + branch, makes atomic commits, then merges back to the shared feature branch and removes its worktree when done.

```bash
git worktree add ../nixos-<feature> -b <feature>
# ... work, commit ...
git worktree remove ../nixos-<feature>
```

## Don't Rebuild During Active Operations

If a build or upgrade is already in progress, do not trigger additional `nix build`, `nixos-rebuild`, or `nix flake update` calls until the user confirms it is safe to do so.
